SIMPLE: syncopation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syncopation
<hw>Syn`co*pa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The act of syncopating; the contraction of a
word by taking one or more letters or syllables from the middle;
syncope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The act of syncopating; a peculiar
figure of rhythm, or rhythmical alteration, which consists in welding
into one tone the second half of one beat with the first half of the
beat which follows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syncope</ent>⟦br⟧
